ityajya&quot;), wh=\r\nere &quot;everything&quot; inlcudes body, name, wife, children, properties etc, then =\r\nanything bad (or good) happening to those entities will not touch one or bi=\r\nnd one. One is &quot;free&quot; from those happenings. *That* liberation is what Lord=\r\n says he shall give and the pre-condition is to give up any sense of duty/r=\r\nesponsibility towards anything.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nThough some =\r\npeople interpret &quot;dharma&quot; in this verse as a religious path, the real meani=\r\nng of dharma is &quot;duty, that which is correct&quot;. We have a sense of responsib=\r\nility towards so many entities, stemming from our conditioning (vasana). Th=\r\nis includes a sense of responsibility towards body, name, wife, children, p=\r\narents, relatives, community, country, religion, subjects of study (e.g. Jy=\r\notish) etc etc. Every sense of &quot;I need to do this&quot;, whether noble or evil, =\r\ncomes from one&#39;s conditioning and *binds* one. If one surrenders all these,=\r\n i.e. effectively one surrenders one&#39;s entire conditioning, at Lord&#39;s feet =\r\nand accepts whatever happens to one as god&#39;s prasad, then one is liberated.=\r\n\n=C2=A0\nBased on the &quot;momentum&quot; from actions before liberation, one may fac=\r\ne various life situations even after liberation. In one case, one may get c=\r\nancer and die. In another case, one may roam the world and spread Sanatana =\r\nDharma. In another case, one may sit in a cave and meditate for 10,000 more=\r\n years. In another case, one may roam the streets looking like a mad person=\r\n. In another case, one may continue to work as a day labourer. In another c=\r\nase, one may destroy a kingdom in a battle. And so on. In all these cases, =\r\nthe liberated being has surrendered all preferences, all likes and dislikes=\r\n, all agendas, attachments and sense of resposibility towards everything on=\r\ne has (body, name, wife, children etc and all attributes of the body-mind c=\r\nomplex that once ruled the roost) and engages in spontaneous actions based =\r\non the circumstances one finds oneself in, based on pre-existing momentum. =\r\nNothing that happens to one binds one and nothing that one does binds one.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nLiberation does not mean that all of one&#39;s belongings (body, name, f=\r\namily, community etc) are &quot;safe&quot; and &quot;well&quot;. Nor does it mean that one does=\r\n nothing. Things may keep happening to one and one may keep doing things. Y=\r\net, one is untouched by them, like a water drop on a lotus leaf, because on=\r\ne has no desires, demands, preferences or agendas and accepts whatever Lord=\r\n gives.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nOne who tells Krishna, &quot;I surrender to=\r\n you. I will not follow any religion or rituals or gods and just pray to yo=\r\nu. So forgive all my sins and make sure that only good things befall my bod=\r\ny, my name, my family etc [because I really care about them and any damage =\r\nto them will upset me]&quot; has missed the point big time! The sublime verse yo=\r\nu referred to is like the culmination of entire Bhagavad Gita and is the es=\r\nsence of all Upanishads.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nOne word of caution. =\r\nIMHO, what follows is far more relevant to most readers of this writeup tha=\r\nn what lies above!\n=C2=A0\nThis verse is the essence of Self-knowledge. But =\r\nmost people of this era are unlikely to realize Self (until the end of this=\r\n yuga cycle). So my suggestion is to set more reasonable goals. It is ok if=\r\n you haven&#39;t surrendered all of your dharmas to Lord.\n=C2=A0\n!!!!! In fact,=\r\n even if you try, you will probably end up misusing that notion to run away=\r\n from most of your higher (and selfless) dharmas and yet end up sticking to=\r\n your lowest and most selfish dharmas (e.g. dharma towards body and its sur=\r\nvival instinct, very tough to shake off). That is useless. !!!!! \n=C2=A0\nNo=\r\n wonder Vedanta comes at the end of all Veda and the verse above comes afte=\r\nr so many chapters on so many other things. Don&#39;t jump to it right away!\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nFirst *expand* your sense of self and your sense of responsibility a=\r\nnd attachment to be more inclusive. Current body-mind complex we inhabit is=\r\n a very limited notion of self. Expand it to family, then to community, the=\r\nn to town, then to nation etc. Or may be to a large community of people wit=\r\nh certain attributes. Basically, try to put others before you, learn to sac=\r\nrifice and engage in more selfless actions than selfish actions. Not everyo=\r\nne may be liberated in this life, but everyone can make SOME progress towar=\r\nds it!\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spirituality Res=\r\nources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 \n\n\n&gt;__________=\r\n______________________\n&gt; From: Sriraman Annaswamy &lt;sriraman@...&gt;\n&gt;T=\r\no: &quot;JyotishWritings-owner@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;JyotishWritings-owner@yahoogrou=\r\nps.com&gt; \n&gt;Cc: Vedic Wisdom &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt;; &quot;vedic-astrology=\r\n@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-astrology@yahoogroups.com&gt;; &quot;JyotishGroup@yahoogro=\r\nups.com&quot; &lt;JyotishGroup@yahoogroups.com&gt;; &quot;JyotishWritings@yahoogroups.com&quot; =\r\n&lt;JyotishWritings@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;Sent: Tuesday, March 5, 2013 1:40 AM\n&gt;S=\r\nubject: Re: [JyotishWritings] Re: Karma, Phala, Remedies, Blessings, Curses=\r\n etc (Re: few questions)\n&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt;Sorry Narasimha, Verse 66 of the Bhagawad Gi=\r\nta is very clear isn&#39;t it - sarva papebyo=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;Is it your position th=\r\nat when Sri Krishna states sarva papebyo, he is excluding prarabda karma an=\r\nd referring solely to sanchita and agami karma or am I missing something?\n&gt;=\r\n\n&gt;\n&gt;Sriraman\n&gt;Sydney, AUS\n&gt;\n&gt;Sent from my iPad\n&gt;\n&gt;On 05/03/2013, at 15:33, =\r\n&quot;Narasimha P.V.R. Rao&quot; &lt;pvr108@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt;Namaste,\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Some quick miscellaneous replies to a few selected questions/comme=\r\nnts that came in response to my writeup yesterday.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Comment 1: &quot;If the remedial measures can only push the karma p=\r\nhala down to manifest \nat a later date/birth then isn&#39;t it a futile=C2=A0ex=\r\nercise. Why not accept \nwhatever comes our way as &#39;PRASAD&#39; from Isvara and =\r\nmove on.&quot;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;My response: The final goal is indeed to reach a state=\r\n of mind where one can accept the fruits of all karmas as prasad of Lord, w=\r\nith an equanimous mind. However, it is not easy. When we receive the fruits=\r\n of some really terrible karmas, our mind gets so twisted and agitated that=\r\n we lose our balance and our judgment gets badly beated. This may result in=\r\n further bad karmas being committed in that agitated/confused state.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt;Thus, it IS sometimes useful to push off some really bad impending ka=\r\nrmas when one is still in a position to do so. If one reaches a calmer stat=\r\ne of mind in that borrowed time, one may be able to handle the bad fruits b=\r\netter. It is even possible theoretically that one pushes off a really bad k=\r\narma, makes progress during that borrowed\n time, reaches an equanimous stat=\r\ne of mind, becomes liberated and then faces the karma as a liberated being =\r\nwith a totally equanimous mind that does not get agitated.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Comment 2: Prarabda karma is which was already done =\r\nand sanchitha and agami are what we going to do.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;My Response: Ac=\r\ntually sanchita karmas are also karmas already done. Sanchita means &quot;piled =\r\nup&quot;. Prarabdha karmas are different in the sense that their fructification =\r\nhas already begun. The verb &quot;prArabh&quot; means &quot;to begin&quot;. Its noun form &quot;prAr=\r\nambha&quot; means &quot;beginning&quot; and its gerund noun form &quot;prArabdha&quot; means &quot;the [o=\r\nne that was] begun&quot;. Prarabdha karmas are actions for which the process of =\r\nreaction has already begun and in the pipeline. Whereas sanchita karmas are=\r\n piled up karmas that have not kicked off their fruits yet. They can be del=\r\nayed indefinitely. If one becomes liberated while living, one can merge in =\r\nCosmic Self without experiencing the fruits of sanchita karmas. However, fr=\r\nuits of prarabdha karmas are already in the pipeline and need to be experie=\r\nnced even by a liberated being.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Though fruits of prarabdha karma=\r\ns are already in the pipeline, even they can actually be delayed or manipul=\r\nated. Bottomline is that there are agents of delivery at the physical and s=\r\nubtle level even for things deep in the pipeline and hence some limited adj=\r\nustment is possible.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Comment 3:How =\r\ndoes nishkam karma works? In other words, when a doer detaches himself from=\r\n an action, where does the reaction goes?\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;My Response: If one id=\r\nentifies with a body-mind complex and a limited sense of self-identificatio=\r\nn and pursues its selfish agenda, one keeps accumulating karmas. But, if on=\r\ne has minimal identification with a body-mind complex to just sustain it, p=\r\nursues no agenda and engages in whatever action is natural in the situation=\r\n one is in (but not driven by any conditioning, i.e. agendas or desires or =\r\nlikes/dislikes), then one is untouched by karmas performed in that state.\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;In the words of Swami Sivananda of Hrishikesh, &quot;The accumulated a=\r\nnd current actions of a Jnani take shelter in Brahmanda Prakriti&quot;. In other=\r\n words, Sanchita karmas (piled up actions from past that have not yet begun=\r\n fructifying) and aagami karmas (actions being performed right now) of a li=\r\nberated being take shelted in\n Cosmic Kinetic Consciousness (Brahmanda Prak=\r\nriti).\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Comment 4: If my destiny is to =\r\nsuffer, why should I pray to God? And if i am being \npunished for some kind=\r\n of bad karma from the past, why am i not aware of it? It is like getting p=\r\nunishment without knowing your bad deeds.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;My Response: One need =\r\nnot pray to God.All one needs to do is to stop engaging in problematic karm=\r\nas to add to the pile of such karmas from the past. More importantly, one n=\r\needs to reach a calm and sustainable state of mind in which that can be mai=\r\nntained even in the middle of a tumultous hurricane caused in one&#39;s life du=\r\ne to serious bad karmas from the past. Once serious troubles set in or mind=\r\n focuses on sense objects, material world and one&#39;s pleasures and pains, mi=\r\nnd tends to lose its balance and judgment, starts pursuing its limited self=\r\nish agendas and starts performing even more bad karmas. Thus, praying to Go=\r\nd and contemplating various ideals and qualities that God represents can gi=\r\nve a shelter to the mind in which it can maintain some calmness, balance an=\r\nd judgment. If that is not the case for one, perhaps one needs to perfect i=\r\nt further.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;God has no agenda to either punish you or hide the re=\r\nason. God is an impartial balancer of reactions to all actions. If there is=\r\n something unreasonable about the reaction you are getting, it means your a=\r\nction had a similar unreasonableness.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0Let me turn around your qu=\r\nestion on being &quot;aware&quot; and ask a simple question. When we cause loss or hu=\r\nrt to someone, do we always tell that person why we are doing it? If not, h=\r\now can we expect someone to tell us before causing loss or hurt to us? If I=\r\n caused terrible strife to someone pious and pure for no reason, then Natur=\r\ne will use someone in future to cause terrible strife to me despite my piet=\r\ny and purity and apparently for no reason.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;In fact, what will yo=\r\nu achieve by knowing exactly what was the action that caused what is happen=\r\ning to you right now? Why is that useful? More useful is your conscience (a=\r\n representation of God in each heart) that tells you right from wrong. It c=\r\nonstantly gives guidance on which actions will give good reactions *in futu=\r\nre*.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Comment 5: Vasana can be for we=\r\nalth, fame, power, domination (a struggle for power!) etc. Many ripus, many=\r\n reasons...!\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;My Response: Well-said. Though we are discussing ka=\r\nrma and karma phala here, the root cause of karma is vasana in chittaakasha=\r\n. (Chidaakaasha is the space of pure consciousness and chittaakaasha is the=\r\n space of conditioned consciousness that has likes, dislikes, desires, agen=\r\ndas etc.) Vasishtha defined liberation as overcoming vasanas in Yoga Vaasis=\r\nhtham and Patanjali defined yoga as &quot;chitta vR^itti nirodhaH yogaH&quot; (resist=\r\ning the working of conditioning is oneness with Cosmic Self) in Yoga Sutras=\r\n. Until we overcome our vasanas, we are bound. Some are dense and some are =\r\nvery subtle. But all of them bind us.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;Comment 6:1. As per Shri Vimalananda, you may also offer all the karmas as=\r\n Homa to inner \ndevas or ishta devta? He mentioned that there is lesser of =\r\nsuffering if \nyou do that. Who gets the remaining delta suffering?\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;My Response: Karmaphala for a specific karma is not a function of that k=\r\narma alone. It is a function of that karma and one&#39;s current state of mind.=\r\n If someone serves spoiled food, one may get an upset stomach for half day =\r\nor diaria for a week. It depends on how strong one is. Similarly, the same =\r\nkarmaphala set in motion by the same external agents of delivery (physical =\r\n& subtle) can cause different reaction inside one, depending on one&#39;s curre=\r\nnt state of mind.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;An idle mind is devil&#39;s workshop. Our minds ke=\r\nep vibrating with various notions and thoughts. A mind vibrating with selfi=\r\nsh desires and unnecessary clutter/confusion *amplifies* the negative effec=\r\nts of one&#39;s environment (through which fruits of karmas are\n administered).=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;If one thinks of ishta devata with reverence and contemplates v=\r\narious ideals and qualities of ishta devata and mind vibrates with saattwik=\r\n energy, it absorbs the negative effects of one&#39;s environment better or at =\r\nleast does not amplify them.\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;Best regards,\n&gt;&gt;Narasimha\n&gt;&gt;-------=\r\n-\n&gt;&gt;Astrology & Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n&gt;&gt;--=\r\n------\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;________________________________\n&gt;&gt;&g